# Project Rules: Unity Game

> 3D/2D game built with Unity 2022+ and C#.

## Project Identity

- **Type**: Game Application
- **Language**: C# (.NET Standard 2.1)
- **Engine**: Unity 2022 LTS+
- **Rendering**: URP (Universal Render Pipeline)
- **Testing**: Unity Test Framework (NUnit)

---

## Coding Standards

### Naming Conventions

| Element | Convention | Example |
|---------|-----------|---------|
| MonoBehaviours | PascalCase | `PlayerController.cs` |
| ScriptableObjects | PascalCase with `SO` suffix | `WeaponDataSO.cs` |
| Private fields | `_camelCase` | `_currentHealth` |
| Public properties | PascalCase | `MaxHealth` |
| Events | PascalCase with `On` prefix | `OnPlayerDeath` |
| Coroutines | PascalCase with `Co` prefix | `CoFadeOut()` |
| Constants | PascalCase | `MaxPlayers` |

### File Organization

```
Assets/
├── Scripts/
│   ├── Player/          # Player-related scripts
│   ├── Enemy/           # Enemy AI
│   ├── UI/              # UI controllers
│   ├── Managers/        # Singleton managers
│   ├── Data/            # ScriptableObjects
│   └── Utils/           # Helper utilities
├── Prefabs/             # Reusable GameObjects
├── Scenes/              # Game scenes
├── Materials/           # Materials & shaders
├── Animations/          # Animation clips & controllers
├── Audio/               # Sound effects & music
└── Resources/           # Runtime-loaded assets
```

---

## Critical Rules (🔴)

### Rule 1: ❌ Never use `Find()` at runtime

```csharp
// ❌ BAD — expensive runtime lookup
void Update() {
    var player = GameObject.Find("Player");
}

// ✅ GOOD — cache reference
[SerializeField] private Transform _player;

void Start() {
    if (_player == null)
        _player = GameObject.FindWithTag("Player").transform;
}
```

### Rule 2: ❌ Never allocate in Update loops

```csharp
// ❌ BAD — GC allocation every frame
void Update() {
    var enemies = new List<Enemy>();
    var hits = Physics.RaycastAll(transform.position, transform.forward);
}

// ✅ GOOD — pre-allocate and reuse
private readonly List<Enemy> _enemyCache = new();
private readonly RaycastHit[] _hitBuffer = new RaycastHit[10];

void Update() {
    _enemyCache.Clear();
    int hitCount = Physics.RaycastNonAlloc(transform.position, transform.forward, _hitBuffer);
}
```

### Rule 3: ✅ Use SerializeField for Inspector references

```csharp
// ❌ BAD — public fields expose internal state
public float speed = 5f;

// ✅ GOOD — private with SerializeField
[SerializeField] private float _speed = 5f;
public float Speed => _speed;
```

---

## Important Guidelines (🟠)

- Use object pooling for frequently spawned/destroyed objects
- Prefer `CompareTag("Tag")` over `gameObject.tag == "Tag"`
- Use ScriptableObjects for shared data instead of singletons when possible
- Implement async operations with UniTask instead of coroutines for complex flows

---

## Code Smells to Avoid

| ❌ Smell | ✅ Instead Do |
|----------|--------------|
| Singletons everywhere | Use ScriptableObject events / DI |
| String-based messaging | Use C# events or UnityEvents |
| `Update()` on every script | Use event-driven architecture |
| Deep MonoBehaviour inheritance | Prefer composition over inheritance |
| Magic numbers | Use serialized fields or constants |
